data.description: Elwyn Avenue offers the charm and workmanship of the 1930's. Upon entering, you're welcomed  by the staircase to the second level and the large living room with neutral tone Wall to Wall carpet. The dining room has ample space for large family gatherings. The kitchen has a snack bar that sections the kitchen and dining with a huge pass thru framed glassless window. An addition has been added next to the kitchen which serves as a family room with French doors leading to a huge covered deck. The rear yard has been fenced in with plenty of space for those outdoor s'more fires. The 7X11 upstairs hallway can be a sitting area to relax and read a book. The main bedroom has a huge closet. This home has so much character and awaits its new owners to add their decorative touches.
